		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001284_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Birkenhead</placeName> 9<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1858</p>
<lb/><p>Dear <persName>Captain Washington</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I enclose for 
<lb/>your consideration the 
<lb/>account which <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Kirk</persName> has handed to 
<lb/>me and would only 
<lb/>remark that he 
<lb/>asked my permission 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001284_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>to buy the strychnine<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I told him to buy 
<lb/>it on my account 
<lb/>(for poisoning animals 
<lb/>without injury to their 
<lb/>skins) and offered 
<lb/>to pay it myself. He 
<lb/>prefers to put it in 
<lb/>this account. I do 
<lb/>not put my name 
<lb/>to it as I do not </p>


	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001284_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'--> 
<addSpan spanTo="#p2r-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left margin of fo. 2r'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p>I am still ready to pay for the 
<lb/>Strychnine.</p><anchor xml:id="p2r-01"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">know whether you would 
<lb/>approve of it seeing the 
<lb/>pay has been running 
<lb/>on since the first 
<lb/>of February and the 
<lb/>duty has not been 
<lb/>very arduous. However 
<lb/>if it is right I shall 
<lb/>be glad to know &amp; 
<lb/>act accordingly. <choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he 
<lb/>seeds were a few pounds 
<lb/>in weight only<reg>.</reg></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001284_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'-->
<lb/><p>6 1/2 <hi rend="underline">o</hi>clock</p>
<lb/><p>The weather here is excessively 
<lb/>bad. The Pilot says it 
<lb/>would be madness to 
<lb/>go out. We meet again 
<lb/>at 10 A.M. tomorrow<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>All are ready at a 
<lb/>moment<reg>'</reg>s notice and 
<lb/>nothing but the weather 
<lb/>prevents our going<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p>I sent my last accounts for presents 
<lb/>yesterday. They are under £300 - &amp; with 
<lb/>the £107 for machinery allowed by the F.O. under £400<reg>.</reg></p>
			
